OL,3,CGroundbreaking 'artificial pancreas'
OL,4,Coffered to type 1 diabetes patients
OL,6,FLocal systems will start identifying
OL,7,Feligible people living with type 1
OL,8,Fdiabetes who health chiefs believe
OL,9,Fcould benefit from the Hybrid Closed
OL,10,FLoop system - sometimes called an
OL,11,Fartificial pancreas.
OL,13,FThere are currently 269,095 people
OL,14,Fliving in England with type 1 diabetes.
OL,16,FThe technology will mean some people
OL,17,Fwith type 1 diabetes will no longer
OL,18,Fneed to inject themselves with insulin
OL,19,Fbut rely on technology to receive this
OL,20,Flife saving medication.
